cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition from video data. Additionally, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it proposes a novel model for capturing inter-related dynamics between interacting people. The paper also involves experiments on datasets, which may make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the proposed model may have applications in robotics (cs.RO) for human-robot interaction.
